    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-03-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-03-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="1056"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1056">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Sampson</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-03-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 4, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 19.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have been personally waited upon by the
                    minister of foreign relations of this Republic, who, in the name of President
                    Alfaro and of the Republic, expressed the fullest sympathy over the <hi
                        rend="italic">Maine</hi> disaster, and desired me to assure President
                    McKinley that no nation is in fuller sympathy and accord with the United States
                    than Ecuador.</p>
                <p>This was meant to be the more emphatic because not merely formal and in
                    writing.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Archibald J. Sampson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
